The article discusses the economic plan of President Biden and its focus on improving economic opportunity and outcomes for all Americans, including Black Americans. It highlights the progress that has been made under the President's leadership, such as record low Black unemployment rates, increased Black household net worth, and the fastest creation rate for Black-owned small businesses in over 25 years. The article also emphasizes the need to address longstanding barriers and outlines two core areas of work: breaking down barriers to wealth building and creating pathways to economic opportunity. It mentions initiatives to expand capital access, provide housing assistance, address student debt, and build pathways to good-paying jobs and digital connectivity. The article concludes by acknowledging that while progress has been made, there is still more work to be done to grow the economy and create economic opportunity for all.